
PROJECT NAME:
Workshop / Bootcamp Registration System

DESCRIPTION:
This is a web-based application developed using PHP and MySQL that allows users to register for workshops and admins to manage events and participants.

OBJECTIVES:
- Participants can browse upcoming workshops and register online.
- Admins can create, update, and delete workshops.
- Admins can view participant lists and feedback.
- System stores user, event, and registration data securely.
- Feedback form and optional certificate generation included.

TECHNOLOGY STACK:
- Frontend: HTML, CSS, Bootstrap
- Backend: PHP
- Database: MySQL
- Optional: PHPMailer (email), FPDF (certificates), Chart.js (analytics)

USER ROLES:
1. Admin
   - Manages workshops (CRUD)
   - Views all participant registrations
   - Views workshop feedback
   - Accesses admin dashboard with analytics
2. Participant
   - Registers/login to the system
   - Views upcoming workshops
   - Registers for workshops
   - Submits feedback after event

MAIN TABLES:
1. users
   - user_id INT (PK)
   - name VARCHAR
   - email VARCHAR
   - password VARCHAR
   - role ENUM('admin', 'participant')

2. workshops
   - workshop_id INT (PK)
   - title, description, date, time, location, seats INT

3. registrations
   - registration_id INT (PK)
   - user_id (FK)
   - workshop_id (FK)
   - status ENUM('confirmed', 'cancelled')
   - reg_date TIMESTAMP

4. feedback
   - feedback_id INT (PK)
   - user_id (FK)
   - workshop_id (FK)
   - rating INT
   - comments TEXT

KEY FEATURES TO GENERATE:
- Login & Register forms with role-based redirection
- Workshop list with seat availability
- Workshop detail page with register button
- Admin workshop management panel
- Participant feedback submission
- Admin dashboard with workshop/user statistics
- Secure password handling with password_hash
- Database connection using `mysqli` or PDO

OPTIONAL ADD-ONS:
- Send confirmation email using PHPMailer after registration
- Generate certificate PDF using FPDF after feedback submission
- Chart.js dashboard for admin (e.g., bar chart of registrations)

GOALS:
Build a secure, clean, scalable PHP-MySQL system that supports both admin and participant roles, and provides complete workshop lifecycle management — from creation to registration to feedback.
*/

